parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear door or liftgate can cause injury to occupants, especially children, and lead to accidents or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The rear door or liftgate falls down unexpectedly
fails to close properly
detaches from the hinge
or opens while driving
causing potential harm to occupants or damage to the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the hood to fly open while driving, obstructing the driver's view, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The hood flies open while driving
breaking the windshield
the hood latch bolt separates from the hood
the hood latch will not release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the liftgate latch can cause the liftgate to fall, hit people, or open while driving, potentially leading to injuries or accidents.
symptoms: The liftgate latch fails
the liftgate falls
the liftgate hits people
the liftgate opens while driving
the liftgate latch is intermittent
the liftgate latch light comes on indicating the latch is open.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine valve guide can cause excessive oil consumption, smoke in the exhaust, and potentially lead to engine fires, which can result in accidents or total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: Excessive oil consumption
smoke in the exhaust
rough engine idle
hesitation
stalling
and engine fires.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air aspirator valve can cause hot exhaust fumes to enter the engine compartment, potentially leading to under-hood fires or exhaust gases entering the passenger compartment, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Hot exhaust fumes in the engine compartment
melting of rubber hoses and plastic components
and potential for under-hood fires or exhaust gases entering the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fires can cause accidents, injuries, or total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: Engine fires
smoke
and flames in the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure, which can result in accidents or strand the driver.
symptoms: Engine overheating
rough engine idle
and engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of engine gaskets can cause oil leaks, which can lead to engine fires or damage, potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Oil leaks
engine fires
and engine damage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective muffler can cause excessive noise, potentially leading to driver distraction or accidents.
symptoms: Excessive noise from the exhaust system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can lead to serious injury or even ejection from the vehicle in the event of an accident, compromising the safety of the occupants.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to retract or lock
the seat belt release button does not function
difficulty in unlatching the seat belt buckle
the seat belt buckle becomes inoperative
the seat belt traps the occupant inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inoperative seat belt buckle can cause the occupant to become trapped inside the vehicle, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not release
the seat belt buckle becomes stuck
difficulty in unlatching the seat belt buckle
the occupant is trapped inside the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to fail to lock or retract, compromising the safety of the occupants in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt fails to lock
the seat belt becomes loose or detached.
